CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1941, pg. 5, reads: "Chesterfield Girls Make Hill Youngsters Happy - Pictured above in foreground are nine of the thirteen youngsters who were donated memberships to the Centre Avenue 'Y' by the Chesterfield Girls of Pittsburgh this week. The club is composed of young women interested in bettering conditions in general for HIll district youngsters.  In the back row are, Malvin Goode, Boys' secretary at the "Y" and the Chesterfield Girls, Mary Palmer, Jeanette Paige, Kathleen Holloway, Ann Mays, Charlene Coles and Arnetta Green, president of the club. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mal Goode, Chesterfield Girls members from left: Mary Palmer, Jeanette Paige, Kathleen Holloway, Ann Mays, Charlene Coles, Arnetta Green, and nine boys, posed possibly in Centre Avenue YMCA
